  author={Kharchenko, Alexander D. and Zyubin, Vladimir E. and Rozov, Andrei S.},
  booktitle={2022 IEEE 23rd International Conference of Young Professionals in Electron Devices and Materials (EDM)}, 
  title={Towards E-Learning Support for Advanced PLC-Programming: Virtual Training Kit for a Sluice Controller with the poST Language}, 
  year={2022},
  volume={},
  number={},
  pages={708-713},
  abstract={The paper discusses an approach to the development of a virtual training kit for practical support of the course on process-oriented languages and advanced PLC programming technologies. The course is focused on the poST language which is a process-oriented extension of the IEC 61131–3 ST language. We offer a development methodology that covers the PLC program development. We describe step by step the process of creating a virtual training kit: we describe specification, create a cyber-physical diagram, program the digital twin of the plant, describe the requirements in the EDTL language, create a poST-program and debug it together with the plant. We demonstrate the proposed approach using an example of sluice automation. The IEC 61131–3 CODESYS development environment is used as the basic programming tool. The plant simulator is implemented by regular visualization of CODESYS. The user interface provides manual control and indication. In conclusion, we discuss the result obtained.},
